<plot>Filmed over a lengthy period, Junction House Blues observes the creative struggles of an unusual group of musicians - some of whom have unidentified intellectual disabilities - where definitions of disability, talent, dysfunction and equality are all blown wide open. It's a funny, sad and 'mad' rock-doc about great music, bad behavior, breaking away and challenging what the world thinks is normal just by being yourself.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?281543</url></doc>
